## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js v18+
- Rust v1.75+
- Stellar CLI
- PostgreSQL v14+
- Docker (optional)

### Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/stellartech.git
cd stellartech
npm install

Environment Setup
cp .env.example .env
cp apps/api/.env.example apps/api/.env
cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env

Configure Stellar (Testnet)
export STELLAR_NETWORK=testnet
export STELLAR_RPC_URL=https://soroban-testnet.stellar.org

stellar keys generate admin --network testnet
stellar keys generate deployer --network testnet

Build & Deploy Contracts
cd contracts
cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --release

stellar contract deploy \
  --wasm target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/disbursement.wasm \
  --source deployer \
  --network testnet

Database Setup
npm run db:migrate
npm run db:seed

Run Development Servers
npm run dev


Frontend: http://localhost:3000

API: http://localhost:3001

Environment Variables
Backend (apps/api/.env)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/stellartech

STELLAR_NETWORK=testnet
STELLAR_RPC_URL=https://soroban-testnet.stellar.org
STELLAR_HORIZON_URL=https://horizon-testnet.stellar.org

DISBURSEMENT_CONTRACT_ID=
ASSET_CONTRACT_ID=
TRADING_CONTRACT_ID=

OPENAI_API_KEY=
JWT_SECRET=
ENCRYPTION_KEY=

Frontend (apps/web/.env)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_NETWORK=testnet

Testing
npm test


Component-level testing:

cargo test
npm run test:api
npm run test:web
npm run test:e2e

Deployment
Smart Contracts (Mainnet)
export STELLAR_NETWORK=mainnet

stellar contract deploy \
  --wasm target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/disbursement.wasm \
  --source deployer \
  --network mainnet

Backend
docker build -t stellartech-api -f apps/api/Dockerfile .
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

Frontend
npm run build:web
vercel --prod

Documentation

docs/ARCHITECTURE.md

